sql: SELECT d_year, s_city, p_brand , SUM(lo_revenue) - SUM(lo_supplycost) AS profit FROM ssb.p_lineorder LEFT JOIN ssb.dates ON lo_orderdate = d_datekey LEFT JOIN ssb.customer ON lo_custkey = c_custkey LEFT JOIN ssb.supplier ON lo_suppkey = s_suppkey LEFT JOIN part ON lo_partkey = p_partkey WHERE c_region = 'AMERICA' AND s_nation = 'UNITED STATES' AND (d_year = 1997 OR d_year = 1998) AND p_category = 'MFGR#04' GROUP BY d_year, s_city, p_brand ORDER BY d_year, s_city, p_brand
